## Percent Change vs Percent Difference

These are different formulas — using the wrong one will give the wrong answer:

- **"Percent change"** from A to B: `(B - A) / A × 100` — denominator is the starting value
- **"Absolute percent change"**: `|B - A| / A × 100`
- **"Percent difference"** between A and B: `|A - B| / ((A + B) / 2) × 100` — denominator is the **average** of both values

⚠️ When the question says "percent difference" (not "change"), use the symmetric/average formula.

